727353f-a.title: Queens: Maspeth Avenue - 54th Street
727353f-a.text:
Maspeth Ave. (left), east from about 54th Street to 58th Street, showing in the background south of Maspeth Ave. on the east side of 58th Street, from left to right, the Queens Head Tavern, at the corner, the Maurice house, in the center, and the Episcopal dhurch of St. Saviours. Across this view are also shown the tracks and right of
way of the Long lIaland Railroad.
March 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

727352f-a.title: Queens: Maspeth Avenue - 54th Street
727352f-a.text:
(1)
Maspeth Ave., west from about 54th Street, showing a westward view of Furman's Island; which was in 1929 a part of Queens County mainland. In the background is seen smoke stacks and a gas tank on the ~ing's County
side.
September 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
(2)
The same, showing a close up of the background seen in View No. 1.
This view was taken from about 48th Street.
September 1929.
Eugene L. Armbruster.
